<subSubSection pageNumber="677" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="677">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="677">Note:</emphasis>
The application of this name is uncertain. Barneby (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="677">Mem. New York. Bot. Gard.</emphasis>
65: 777. 1991) treated it as a 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="677">species incertae sedis</emphasis>
and did not trace a type. He noted that if the name proved to apply to a true 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="677">Mimosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the armature and leaf-formula would fit 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barneby" authorityYear="1991" baseAuthorityName="DC." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="distachya" variety="oligacantha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="677">M. distachya</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="677">oligacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(DC.) Barneby. A Clifford collection (BM), only rather doubtfully associated with the name, is not a 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="677">Mimosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Humb. &amp; Bonpl. ex Willd." authorityName="Willd." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Acacia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macracantha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="677">Acacia macracantha</emphasis>
Humb. &amp; Bonpl. ex Willd.
</taxonomicName>
, a very large and widely distributed complex in the neotropics (Rico, pers. comm.). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="semispinosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="677">Mimosa semispinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be a candidate for rejection.
</paragraph>
